# ============================================================
# Sip or Slip — Environment Variables
# ============================================================
#
# This project currently runs entirely on the client (Next.js +
# React Three Fiber + zustand). There are NO secrets required to
# build or run it — all vessel data, occasions, and stories live
# in `src/data/` as static TypeScript modules.
#
# This file exists so that:
#   1. Future contributors know where to put secrets if any are added.
#   2. Vercel / Netlify / other hosts see a clear contract.
#   3. Anyone cloning the repo can `cp .env.example .env.local`
#      without breaking the build.
#
# To use: copy this file to `.env.local` (gitignored) and fill in
# real values only when one of the optional features below is
# turned on.
# ============================================================


# ---- Optional: Supabase (cross-session collection persistence) ----
# Currently unused. The collection state lives in zustand /
# sessionStorage. Enable these only if you wire up the Supabase
# client described in ARCHITECTURE.md §2.5.
#
# NEXT_PUBLIC_SUPABASE_URL=https://your-project.supabase.co
# NEXT_PUBLIC_SUPABASE_ANON_KEY=your-anon-key-here


# ---- Optional: Sentry (error reporting) ----
# Currently unused. Add the @sentry/nextjs SDK before enabling.
#
# NEXT_PUBLIC_SENTRY_DSN=https://xxxxx@sentry.io/xxxxx
